This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a variant of variational autoencoders for clustering high dimensional data. It also involves the automatic learning of a tree structure of multiple super latent variables from data, which is a common topic in machine learning research. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the proposed model involves learning a complex structure from data, which is a common theme in AI research. 

Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning methods for clustering, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) research. 

Finally, the paper involves the use of latent variables, which is a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE) research.
